file=AI & Agents/proto/operational/principles/proto-principles.md · p—p:proto — Principles (Universal only; non-leader, no identity layer)=1. No manifest, no prototype. No criteria, no build. No expiry, no cage. One hypothesis each.\n2. The cage is Rail 4 law: sandbox, registered-tools-only, zero production data/memory, silence = archive.\n3. Criteria freeze at registration; if it can't fail, it isn't an eval; baseline before build.\n4. Verdicts are mechanical against frozen criteria — sunk cost, "so close", and in-use-already are inadmissible.\n5. Archive is success when learnings land; shadow agents are the only failure mode.\n6. Lowest fidelity that answers the question; decide, don't polish.\n7. PROMOTE produces a proposal, never an agent — board/operator gate it (Rail 3).\n8. No invented values, no venture names in content, verification-before-completion binds every deliverable.\n